<h1>LLM Cost Per User Benchmarks</h1>
<p class="updated" style="color:#6B7689;font-size:14px;margin-top:-6px">Updated 12 July 2026</p>
<p>Modeled monthly LLM cost per active user by role and team type. Use these benchmarks to compare your spending against similar companies and identify cost optimization opportunities.</p>

<ul class="badge-row">
  <li>Modeled scenarios from published LLM pricing</li>
  <li>Benchmarks by role: developers, analysts, customer-facing</li>
  <li>Includes low, typical, and high-use tiers</li>
  <li>All prices current as of July 2026</li>
</ul>

<h2>Developer Tier (Coding Assistants)</h2>

<p>Developers using AI code generation and debugging consume the highest tokens per user. Typical daily usage: 4–8 hours of IDE time with continuous LLM interactions.</p>

<table>
<thead>
<tr>
  <th>Usage Level</th>
  <th>Daily Interactions</th>
  <th>Est. Monthly Tokens</th>
  <th>Model Mix</th>
  <th>Cost/User/Month</th>
  <th>Notes</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
  <td><strong>Light</strong></td>
  <td>10–20</td>
  <td class="number">5M in / 2M out</td>
  <td>Gemini Flash (80%), Sonnet (20%)</td>
  <td class="number">$35–$45</td>
  <td>Occasional code completions, not relying on LLM for design</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td><strong>Typical</strong></td>
  <td>40–60</td>
  <td class="number">20M in / 10M out</td>
  <td>Opus (70%), Flash (30%)</td>
  <td class="number">$150–$200</td>
  <td>Regular use of chat, debugging, test generation</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td><strong>Heavy</strong></td>
  <td>100+</td>
  <td class="number">50M in / 25M out</td>
  <td>Opus 4.8 (100%)</td>
  <td class="number">$375–$500</td>
  <td>Full-day LLM pair programming, agent-based workflows</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<p><strong>Cost calculation (Typical):</strong> 20M input tokens at Claude Opus 4.8 ($5/M) = $100. 10M output tokens at $25/M = $250. Total: $350, reduced to $150–$200 with model routing (using cheaper models for 40% of queries) and 20% batch savings.</p>

<p><strong>Coding assistant subscription vs. API cost:</strong> GitHub Copilot Pro+ ($39/month) offers 7,000 credits ($70 value), covering ~$70 of monthly API cost. For typical developers, a $20–$100/month subscription plan often beats self-managed API billing.</p>

<h2>Knowledge Worker Tier (Writing, Research, Analysis)</h2>

<p>Analysts, content creators, researchers, and product managers use LLMs for writing, research, and decision support. Moderate token consumption (1–3 hours/day).</p>

<table>
<thead>
<tr>
  <th>Usage Level</th>
  <th>Daily Sessions</th>
  <th>Est. Monthly Tokens</th>
  <th>Model Mix</th>
  <th>Cost/User/Month</th>
  <th>Notes</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
  <td><strong>Light</strong></td>
  <td>5–10</td>
  <td class="number">3M in / 1.5M out</td>
  <td>Flash (90%), Sonnet (10%)</td>
  <td class="number">$8–$12</td>
  <td>Occasional brainstorming, research summaries</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td><strong>Typical</strong></td>
  <td>20–30</td>
  <td class="number">12M in / 6M out</td>
  <td>Sonnet (70%), Opus (30%)</td>
  <td class="number">$35–$50</td>
  <td>Daily writing support, document analysis, idea generation</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td><strong>Heavy</strong></td>
  <td>50+</td>
  <td class="number">30M in / 15M out</td>
  <td>Opus (100%)</td>
  <td class="number">$100–$150</td>
  <td>Research-heavy roles, policy writing, strategic analysis</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<p><strong>Cost calculation (Typical):</strong> 12M input tokens (Sonnet $3/M + Opus $5/M split) ≈ $36. 6M output tokens ≈ $75 (mixed rates). Total: ~$111, reduced to $35–$50 with prompt caching (reusing research documents) and batch processing (overnight analysis).</p>

<p><strong>Optimization tip:</strong> Most knowledge workers can reduce per-user cost to $15–$25 by using cheaper models (Gemini Flash, DeepSeek) for routine tasks and reserving Claude/GPT-5.5 for complex analysis.</p>

<h2>Customer-Facing Tier (Support Agents, Chatbots)</h2>

<p>Customer service chatbots and RAG systems handle high volume but amortize LLM cost across many conversations. Cost per active user is typically calculated as (total monthly LLM spend / concurrent active users).</p>

<table>
<thead>
<tr>
  <th>Deployment Scale</th>
  <th>Monthly Conversations</th>
  <th>Avg Tokens/Conversation</th>
  <th>Model</th>
  <th>Monthly LLM Cost</th>
  <th>Cost per Concurrent User</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
  <td><strong>Small (1,000/mo)</strong></td>
  <td class="number">1,000</td>
  <td class="number">2,000</td>
  <td>Gemini Flash</td>
  <td class="number">$10–$15</td>
  <td class="number">$0.10 (100 concurrent)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td><strong>Medium (10,000/mo)</strong></td>
  <td class="number">10,000</td>
  <td class="number">2,000</td>
  <td>Gemini Flash + caching</td>
  <td class="number">$80–$120</td>
  <td class="number">$0.80 (100 concurrent)</td>
</tr>
<tr>
  <td><strong>Large (100,000/mo)</strong></td>
  <td class="number">100,000</td>
  <td class="number">2,000</td>
  <td>Gemini Flash + batch</td>
  <td class="number">$600–$800</td>
  <td class="number">$6–$8 (100 concurrent)</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

<p><strong>Cost calculation (Medium):</strong> 10,000 conversations × 2,000 tokens ≈ 20M tokens. Gemini 3.5 Flash at $1.50/M input + $9/M output (avg 40% input, 60% output) ≈ $10M @ $1.50/M + $10M @ $9/M = $105. With prompt caching (70% cache hit rate after embedding customer KB), cost drops to ~$40–$50/month.</p>

<p><strong>Key insight:</strong> For chatbots, use low-cost models (Gemini Flash $0.30–$2.50, DeepSeek V4 Flash $0.14–$0.28) with prompt caching to maximize token efficiency. Cost per customer interaction can be as low as $0.001.</p>

<h2>Data Processing Tier (Batch &amp; ETL)</h2>

<p>Teams processing documents, logs, or datasets via LLM batch jobs consume massive token volume but benefit from 50% batch discount on all input/output.</p>

<table>
<thead>
<tr>
  <th>Workload</th>
  <th>Monthly Records</th>
  <th>Avg Tokens/Record</th>
  <th>Model (w/ 50% Batch)</th>
